items.title: Ulta Names Steelman CEO, Kimbell to Retire
items.description: Ulta Beauty has named Kecia Steelman as its chief executive, succeeding David Kimbell, as the company aims to reaccelerate its growth amid a global slowdown in the beauty market.

items.title: 2 Dividend Stocks to Double Up on Right Now
items.description: Walmart (NYSE: WMT) and Home Depot (NYSE: HD) have long histories of raising payouts and should continue providing capital appreciation opportunities.  Walmart has become a household name with its widespread namesake stores and Sam's Club stores.  People continue to see Walmart as a place to shop and spend money.
